From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: SPI clock 4 MHz for hand-wired SD breakout

24 MHz default fails CMD0 with -14 on this breadboard wiring (signal
integrity at high speed). 1 MHz works for init but FATFS writes time
out (file close -EIO). 4 MHz is a middle ground that should be slow
enough for clean signaling on long wires but fast enough for FATFS.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
@@ -13,7 +13,7 @@
             compatible = "zephyr,sdmmc-disk";
             status = "okay";
         };
-        spi-max-frequency = <24000000>;  // 24 MHz SPI speed for SD card
+        spi-max-frequency = <4000000>;  // patch 0017: 4 MHz for breadboard wiring
     };
 };
 &pinctrl {
